Linguistics is wonderful.

Here in the Philippines we have too many dialects even in the Bicol region we have more than 10 variations. Our national language is Filipino, a creole made up of Malayan, Chinese, Japanese, Indonesian, English, Spanish and Tagalog(the native tongue of the Taga-ilog or the river men).

Going by history the Scots are Irish who moved to the area. No wonder you both sound almost the same.

I should really know more German though.
